<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A3206005" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Rear Differential Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A3206003">Rear Differential Assembly Dismounting and Remounting</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A3206004">Rear Differential Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A3206005001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove drive shaft flanges (1) from rear differential.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential cover (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A320010.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.252mm" ver = "01" gw = "109" gh = "120"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove circlips of drive shaft flange.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove drive bevel gear with differential case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove drive bevel gear bolts (1) and then remove drive bevel gear (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320010.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "38.778mm" ver = "02" gw = "123" gh = "93"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential side bearing outer races and differential side bearing inner races (1) from differential case using special tools.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B001">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-60910">
09913–60910
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B002">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-88210">
09925–88210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "44.622mm" ver = "03" gw = "75" gh = "110"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drive out differential pinion shaft pin using special tool and hammer.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B003">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09922-85811">
09922–85811
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.454mm" ver = "02" gw = "84" gh = "107"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out differential pinion shaft and then remove differential side gears (1), differential pinions (2), washers (3) and shims (4) from differential case (5).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320013.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.994mm" ver = "02" gw = "126" gh = "131"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Undo caulking and remove bevel pinion nut using special tool and power wrench (1).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B004">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09930-40113">
09930–40113
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A320011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "53.457mm" ver = "01" gw = "124" gh = "135"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove companion flange (1) from drive bevel pinion, and then drive out drive bevel pinion.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B005">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-65135">
09913–65135
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A320012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "54.701mm" ver = "01" gw = "98" gh = "139"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear bearing (1) from drive bevel pinion (2) using bearing puller (3) and press (4).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.285mm" ver = "02" gw = "111" gh = "118"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove input oil seal from differential carrier.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using a hammer and brass bar (1), drive out front and rear bearing outer races (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A320013.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.365mm" ver = "01" gw = "219" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A3206005002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A3206006">Rear Differential Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Judging from faulty conditions noted before disassembly and what is found through visual check of bearing and gear tooth etc. after disassembly, prepare replacing parts and proceed to reassembly according to procedures as described in the following.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Bevel gear and pinion must be replaced as a set when either replacement becomes necessary.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
When replacing taper roller bearing, replace as inner race &#38; outer race assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit bevel pinion bearing outer races (2) to differential carrier (1) by using special tools and hydraulic press as shown in the figure.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B006">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-75510">
09913–75510
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B007">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-75520">
09913–75520
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A320014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.135mm" ver = "01" gw = "187" gh = "117"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
After applying differential oil to differential side gears (4), differential pinions (5), pinion shaft (3), side washers (1), spring washers (7) and pinion washers (2), install them in differential case (6).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
For correct installing direction of side washers and spring washers, refer to figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320019.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.703mm" ver = "01" gw = "158" gh = "144"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check differential pinion (1) for smooth rotation.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I3RH01322031.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.196mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Align holes of pinion shaft and differential case and drive in differential pinion shaft pin till pin end is flush with end surface of case using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B008">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09922-85811">
09922–85811
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A320042.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.154mm" ver = "01" gw = "113" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Measure back rash and thrust play of differential side gear as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If measured value is out of specification, select suitable differential side gear washer from among the following available size, install it and check again.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B009">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09900-20607">
09900–20607
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B010">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09900-20701">
09900–20701
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B011">
<s-part>
(C)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09952-06010">
09952–06010
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Differential side gear backlash
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Hold differential assembly with soft jawed vise and apply measuring tip of dial gauge to side gear as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Fixing differential pinion, turn differential side gear back and forth and read dial gauge.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<spec>
<title>
Differential side gear backlash
</title>
<ptxt>
0.00 – 0.15 mm (0.000 – 0.005 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Differential side gear thrust play
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Hold differential assembly with soft jawed vise and apply measuring tip of dial gauge to side gear as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Move side gear up and down by hand and read dial gauge.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<spec>
<title>
Differential side gear thrust play
</title>
<ptxt>
0.00 - 0.37 mm (0.000 - 0.014 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>
Available side gear washer thickness
</title>
<ptxt>
0.90, 0.95, 1.00, 1.05, 1.10, 1.15 and 1.20 mm (0.035, 0.037, 0.039, 0.041, 0.043, 0.045 and 0.047 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
</s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A520047.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "91.912mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "244"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Put bevel gear (2) on differential case (3) and tighten bolts (1) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be sure to use new bolt pre-coated with adhesive. Otherwise, bolt may loosen.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T3B006">
<t-part>
Bevel gear bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
78
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
8.0
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
57.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A320043.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.621mm" ver = "01" gw = "149" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit differential side bearings (1) using special tool and hydraulic press (2).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B012">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-76010">
09913–76010
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RS0D320020.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.171mm" ver = "01" gw = "163" gh = "146"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
To engage drive bevel pinion and gear correctly, it is pre-required to install drive bevel pinion to differential carrier properly by using adjusting shim as described on the followings. Shown below is relative positions of drive bevel pinion, differential carrier and mounting dummy.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3B013">
<s-part>
